I just built a multi-player Knowledge Pool deck, and it was great times. [Ornithopter](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Ornithopter)s, [Memnite](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Memnite)s, and [Everflowing Chalice](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Everflowing Chalice)s to retrieve stuff from the Pool for free, and [Leyline of Anticipation](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Leyline of Anticipation) to do it at instant speed! Mages, both Trinket and Treasure, fetch the necessary components, and [Aether Adept](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Aether Adept) ensures that I always have a zero-cost artifact creature to play. [Ponder](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Ponder) and [Foresee](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Foresee) help to set up turns and keep my hand full, and Emrakul is there for shenanigans. My play group hated it.  

